OL,3,CWoman stole man's mobility scooter -
OL,4,Cleaving him to freeze to death
OL,6,FA woman who stole a man's mobility
OL,7,Fscooter, leaving him to freeze to
OL,8,Fdeath in a Tesco carpark in Stroud,
OL,9,Fhas pleaded guilty to manslaughter.
OL,11,FKimberley Ann Hawkins, 41 and of no
OL,12,Ffixed address, admitted to the
OL,13,Fmanslaughter of 63-year-old Neil
OL,14,FShadwick on 22 January 2023.
OL,16,FHawkins previously admitted to
OL,17,Faggravated vehicle taking, in relation
OL,18,Fto Mr Shadwick's mobility scooter,
OL,19,Fwhich he used as his mode of transport.
